msgstr "2.30.00"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:22
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Allows treating audio <acronym>CD</acronym>s like a <quote>real</quote> "
"filesystem, where tracks are represented as files and, when copied from the "
"folder, are digitally extracted from the <acronym>CD</acronym>. This ensures "
"a perfect copy of the audio data."
msgstr ""
"Dozvoljava tretiranje audio <acronym>CD</acronym>ova kao <quote>stvarni</"
"quote> sistem datoteka, gdje su evidencije predstavljene kao trake  i, kada "
"kopirane iz foldera, su digitalno ekstraktovani iz <acronym>CD</acronym>. "
"Ovo osigurava perfektnu kopiju audio traka."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:28
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
#| msgid ""
#| "To see how this slave works, insert an audio <acronym>CD</acronym> in "
#| "your &CD-ROM; drive and type <userinput>audiocd:/</userinput> into "
#| "&konqueror;. Within a few seconds you should see a list of tracks and "
#| "some folders."
msgid ""
"To see how this KIO worker works, insert an audio <acronym>CD</acronym> in "
"your &CD-ROM; drive and type <userinput>audiocd:/</userinput> into "
"&konqueror;. Within a few seconds you should see a list of tracks and some "
"folders."
msgstr ""
"Da bi vidjeli kako ovaj rob radi, ubacite audio <acronym>CD</acronym> u vaš "
"&CD-ROM; i upišite <userinput>audiocd:/</userinput> u &konqueror;. Unutar "
"par sekundi ćete vidjeti listu traka i neke foldere."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:33
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
#| msgid ""
#| "Audio <acronym>CD</acronym>s don't really have folders, but the audiocd "
#| "slave provides them as a convenience. If you look inside these folders "
#| "you will see that they all contain the same number of tracks. If you are "
#| "connected to the Internet, some folders will have the actual track titles "
#| "shown as the filenames."
msgid ""
"Audio <acronym>CD</acronym>s don't really have folders, but the audiocd KIO "
"worker provides them as a convenience. If you look inside these folders you "
"will see that they all contain the same number of tracks. If you are "
"connected to the Internet, some folders will have the actual track titles "
"shown as the filenames."
msgstr ""
"Audio <acronym>CD</acronym>s ustvari nemaju foldere, ali audiocd rob ih "
"pruža kao pogodnost. Ako pogledate unutar foldera vidjet ćete da svi oni "
"sadrže isti broj traka. Ako ste konektovani na internet, neki folderi će "
"imati stvarni naziv trake prikazan kao ime datoteke."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:39
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The reason that these separate folders exist are so that you can choose in "
"which format you would like to listen to (or copy) the tracks on the "
"<acronym>CD</acronym>."
msgstr ""
"Razlog zašto ovi odvojeni folderi postoje je zato da možete izabrati u kojem "
"formatu želite slušati (ili kopirati ) traku na <acronym>CD</acronym>."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:43
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If you drag a track from the <filename class=\"directory\">Ogg Vorbis</"
"filename> folder and drop it on another &konqueror; window open at your home "
"folder, you should see a progress window showing you that the track is being "
"extracted from the <acronym>CD</acronym> and saved to a file. Note that Ogg "
"Vorbis is a compressed format, so the file in your home folder will appear a "
"great deal smaller than it would have been if you had copied the raw data."
msgstr ""
"Ako prevučete traku iz <filename class=\"directory\">Ogg Vorbis</filename> "
"foldera i ispustite ga na drugi &konqueror; prozor otvoren na prvom folderu, "
"trebali bi vidjeti prozor koji prikazuje napredak da se traka ekstraktuje "
"sa  <acronym>CD</acronym> i snimiti u datoteku."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:51
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
#| msgid ""
#| "The mechanism behind this is quite simple. When the audiocd slave is "
#| "asked to retrieve a track from the <filename class=\"directory\">Ogg "
#| "Vorbis</filename> folder, it starts extracting the digital audio data "
#| "from the <acronym>CD</acronym>. As it sends the data over to the file in "
#| "your home folder, it simultaneously encodes it in Ogg Vorbis format "
#| "(<acronym>CD</acronym> audio is in an uncompressed format to start with)."
msgid ""
"The mechanism behind this is quite simple. When the audiocd KIO worker is "
"asked to retrieve a track from the <filename class=\"directory\">Ogg Vorbis</"
"filename> folder, it starts extracting the digital audio data from the "
"<acronym>CD</acronym>. As it sends the data over to the file in your home "
"folder, it simultaneously encodes it in Ogg Vorbis format (<acronym>CD</"
"acronym> audio is in an uncompressed format to start with)."
msgstr ""
"Mehanizam iza ovog je jednostavan. Kada audiocd robu kažete da vrati traku "
"iz <filename class=\"directory\">Ogg Vorbis</filename> foldera, počinje "
"ekstraktovanje digitalnih audio podataka iz <acronym>CD</acronym>. Kako "
"šalje podatke do datoteke na vašem prvom folderu, on istovremeno kodira u "
"Ogg Vorbis formatu (<acronym>CD</acronym> audio je u nekompresovanom formatu "
"na početku)."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:59
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"You could also try dragging a file ending in <literal role=\"extension\">."
"wav</literal> and dropping it on the &kde; Media Player, &juk;. In this "
"case, the procedure that happens behind the scenes is similar, except that "
"instead of encoding the audio data in Ogg Vorbis format, it is put through a "
"very simple conversion, from raw binary data (which the <literal role="
"\"extension\">.cda</literal> files in the toplevel folder represent) to "
"<quote>RIFF WAV</quote> format, a non-compressed format that most media "
"players understand."
msgstr ""
"Također možete pokušati prevlačiti završnu datoteku u <literal role="
"\"extension\">.wav</literal> i ostaviti u &kde; Media Playeru, &juk;. U tom "
"slučaju, procedura koja se dešava iza scena je slična, osim što umjesto "
"kodiranja audio podataka u Ogg Vorbis formatu, pušten je kroz jednostavnu "
"konverzu, kroz sirove binarne podatke ( koji <literal role=\"extension\">."
"cda</literal> datoteke u toplevel folderu reprezentuju) da <quote>RIFF WAV</"
"quote> format, nekompresovane formate koje većina media playera razumije."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:68
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"&juk; should quite happily play the <literal role=\"extension\">.wav</"
"literal> file, but if it has trouble, you may consider using the "
"<option>paranoia_level</option> option, explained below."
msgstr ""
"&juk; treba prilično sretno svirati  <literal role=\"extension\">.wav</"
"literal>  datoteku, ali ako ima problema, možete koirstiti  "
"<option>paranoia_level</option> opciju, objašnjenu ispod."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:74
#, no-c-format
msgid "Options"
msgstr "Postavke"

#. Tag: option
#: index.docbook:77
#, no-c-format
msgid "device"
msgstr "uređaj"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:79
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
#| msgid ""
#| "Set the path to the audio <acronym>CD</acronym> device, &eg; "
#| "<userinput>audiocd:/<option>?device</option>=<parameter>/dev/sdc</"
#| "parameter></userinput>. Normally, the slave will try to find a "
#| "<acronym>CD</acronym> drive with an audio <acronym>CD</acronym> inserted, "
#| "but if it fails or you have more than one <acronym>CD</acronym> drive, "
#| "you may want to try this option. Note that the configuration dialog "
#| "allows you to set a default value for this option."
msgid ""
"Set the path to the audio <acronym>CD</acronym> device, &eg; "
"<userinput>audiocd:/<option>?device</option>=<parameter>/dev/sdc</"
"parameter></userinput>. Normally, the KIO worker will try to find a "
"<acronym>CD</acronym> drive with an audio <acronym>CD</acronym> inserted, "
"but if it fails or you have more than one <acronym>CD</acronym> drive, you "
"may want to try this option. Note that the configuration dialog allows you "
"to set a default value for this option."
msgstr ""
"Napravite put do audio  <acronym>CD</acronym> uređaja, &eg; "
"<userinput>audiocd:/<option>?device</option>=<parameter>/dev/sdc</"
"parameter></userinput>. Normalno, rob će pokušati pronaći <acronym>CD</"
"acronym> disk sa audio <acronym>CD</acronym> interstovanim, ali ako ne "
"uspije ili vi imate više nego jedan <acronym>CD</acronym> disk, željet ćete "
"isprobati ovu opciju. Imajte na umu da vam dijalog konfiguracije omogućava "
"da postavite default vrijednost za ovu opciju."

#. Tag: option
#: index.docbook:90
#, no-c-format
msgid "fileNameTemplate"
msgstr "šablonsko ime datoteke"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:92
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Set the file name template, &eg; <userinput>audiocd:/<option>?"
"fileNameTemplate</option>=<parameter>Track %{number}</parameter></"
"userinput>. Note that the configuration dialog allows you to set a default "
"value for this option. A warning that if you set it to an empty string no "
"files will show up."
msgstr ""
"Postavite šablonsko ime datoteke, &eg; <userinput>audiocd:/<option>Šablonsko "
"ime datoteke</option>=<parameter>Track %{number}</parameter></userinput>. "
"Imajte na umu da vam dijalog konfiguracije dozvoljava da postavite defaultnu "
"vrijednost za ovu opciju. Upozorenje ako stavite na prazno ime nijedna "
"datoteka se neće pojaviti."

#. Tag: option
#: index.docbook:98
#, no-c-format
msgid "albumNameTemplate"
msgstr "šablonsko ime albuma"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:100
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Set the album name template, &eg; <userinput>audiocd:/<option>?"
"albumNameTemplate</option>=<parameter>%{albumartist} %{albumtitle}</"
"parameter></userinput>. Note that the configuration dialog allows you to set "
"a default value for this option."
msgstr ""
"Postavite šablonsko ime albuma, &eg; <userinput>audiocd:/<option>?šablonsko "
"ime albuma</option>=<parameter>%{albumartist} %{albumtitle}</parameter></"
"userinput>. Imajte na umu da vam dijalog konfiguracije dozvoljava da "
"postavite dafaultnu vrijednost za ovu opciju."

#. Tag: option
#: index.docbook:106
#, no-c-format
msgid "niceLevel"
msgstr "dobarLevel"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:108
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Sets the process nice level for encoders, &eg; <userinput>audiocd:/<option>?"
"albumNameTemplate</option>=<parameter>niceLevel=10</parameter></userinput>. "
"Note that the configuration dialog allows you to set a default value for "
"this option."
msgstr ""
"Postavite proces za dobar nivo za kodiranje, &eg; <userinput>audiocd:/"
"<option>?albumNameTemplate</option>=<parameter>niceLevel=10</parameter></"
"userinput>. Imajte na umu da vam dijalog konfiguracije dozvoljava da "
"postavite defaultnu vrijednost za ovu opciju."

#. Tag: option
#: index.docbook:114
#, no-c-format
msgid "paranoia_level"
msgstr "paranoja_nivo"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:116
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Set the amount of error detection and correction used when extracting data."
msgstr ""
"Postavite iznos za detekciju i ispravljanje grešaka pri izvlačenju podataka."

#. Tag: term
#: index.docbook:121
#, no-c-format
msgid "Level 0"
msgstr "Nivo 0"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:123
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"No detection or correction. Only useful if you have a perfect <acronym>CD</"
"acronym> drive (unlikely)."
msgstr ""
"Nema detektovanih korekcija. Jedino korisno ako imate perfektan <acronym>CD</"
"acronym> disk ( nije vjerovatno)."

#. Tag: term
#: index.docbook:129
#, no-c-format
msgid "Level 1"
msgstr "Nivo 1"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:131
#, no-c-format
msgid "Enable basic error checking and correction."
msgstr "Omogućava osnovne provjere i ispravljanja grešaka."

#. Tag: term
#: index.docbook:136
#, no-c-format
msgid "Level 2"
msgstr "Nivo 2"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:138
#, no-c-format
msgid "Default. Specifies that only a perfect extraction will be accepted."
msgstr "Default. Specifikuje da će samo perfektno izdvajanje biti prihvaćene."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:144
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Note that there is a disadvantage to level 2. Extraction can be very slow, "
"so real-time digital playback may not work properly. If you have a good "
"quality <acronym>CD</acronym> drive (note that more expensive does not "
"necessarily mean better quality) then you probably won't experience very "
"slow extraction, but a poor drive may take days (!) to extract the audio "
"from one <acronym>CD</acronym>."
msgstr ""
"Imajte na umu da postoji nedostatak na nivou 2. Izdvajanje može biti vrlo "
"sporo, tako da u realnom vremenu digitalne reprodukcije možda neće ispravno "
"raditi. Ako imate dobru kvalitetu  <acronym>CD</acronym> diska (imajte na "
"umu da skuplje ne znači nužno i kvalitetnije) onda vjerojatno nećete "
"doživjeti vrlo spore ekstrakcije, ali lošem disku može potrajati nekoliko "
"dana (!) za izdvajanje audio iz jednog <acronym>CD</acronym>."

#. Tag: option
#: index.docbook:154
#, no-c-format
msgid "cddbChoice"
msgstr "cddbIzbor"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:157
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Specify which Internet <acronym>CD</acronym> Database entry to use. Audio "
"<acronym>CD</acronym>s don't have track names, but the Internet <acronym>CD</"
"acronym> Database is a clever system which uses a special unique identifier "
"generated from the number and length of tracks on each <acronym>CD</acronym> "
"to cross-reference a track listing. Track listings are contributed by the "
"Internet community and made available to all. Occasionally there will be "
"multiple entries. You can specify which one to use."
msgstr ""
"Specifikujte koji internet <acronym>CD</acronym>unos  baze podataka treba "
"koristiti. Audio <acronym>CD</acronym>s ne posjeduje imena traka, ali "
"internet <acronym>CD</acronym> baza podataka je pametan sistem koji koristi "
"specijalne unikatne identifikatore generirane od brojeva i dužine traka na "
"svakom <acronym>CD</acronym> da upućuje na spisak traka. Spisak traka "
"doprinosi i Internet zajednice i dostupna je svima. Povremeno će biti više "
"ulazaka. Možete odrediti koju koristiti."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:165
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"You can submit your own track listings using &kscd;, the &kde; <acronym>CD</"
"acronym> player."
msgstr ""
"Možete potvriditi vašu listu traka koristeći &kscd;, &kde; <acronym>CD</"
"acronym> player."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:168
#, no-c-format
msgid "By default audiocd tries to pick the best one."
msgstr "Po defaultu audiocd pokušava da izabere najbolji."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:174
#, no-c-format
msgid "Examples"
msgstr "Primjeri"

#. Tag: userinput
#: index.docbook:176
#, no-c-format
msgid "audiocd:/?device=/dev/scd0&amp;paranoia_level=0&amp;cddbChoice=0"
msgstr "audiocd:/?device=/dev/scd0&amp;paranoia_level=0&amp;cddbChoice=0"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:178
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Gives a listing of the tracks on the audio <acronym>CD</acronym> inserted in "
"<filename class=\"devicefile\">/dev/scd0</filename>, which on &Linux; "
"specifies the first <acronym>SCSI</acronym> &CD-ROM; device. If you copy "
"tracks from the <acronym>CD</acronym>, digital extraction will be performed "
"without error correction or detection. The <acronym>CDDB</acronym> Database "
"entry 0 will be used."
msgstr ""
"Daje listu traka na audio <acronym>CD</acronym> insertovanih u  <filename "
"class=\"devicefile\">/dev/scd0</filename>, koji na &Linux; specifira prvi "
"<acronym>SCSI</acronym> &CD-ROM;  uređaj. Ako kopirate trake iz <acronym>CD</"
"acronym>, digitalna ekstrakcija će biti urađena bez korekcije i detektovanja "
"grešaka. <acronym>CDDB</acronym> dostupnost baze podataka 0 će biti "
"iskorišten."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:189
#, no-c-format
msgid "Frequently Asked Question"
msgstr "Često postavljena pitanja"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:192
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"I get <errorname>The file or folder / does not exist</errorname>. How do I "
"fix that? I have an audio <acronym>CD</acronym> in my drive!"
msgstr ""
"Dobijem <errorname> Datoteka ili folder / ne postoji</errorname>. Kako da "
"popravim to? Imam audio <acronym>CD</acronym> u disku."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:198
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
#| msgid ""
#| "Try running <userinput><command>cdparanoia</command> <option>-vsQ</"
#| "option></userinput> as yourself (not <systemitem class=\"username\">root</"
#| "systemitem>). Do you see a track list? If not, make sure you have "
#| "permission to access the <acronym>CD</acronym> device. If you're using "
#| "<acronym>SCSI</acronym> emulation (possible if you have an <acronym>IDE</"
#| "acronym> <acronym>CD</acronym> writer) then make sure you check that you "
#| "have read and write permissions on the generic <acronym>SCSI</acronym> "
#| "device, which is probably <filename class=\"devicefile\">/dev/sg0</"
#| "filename>, <filename class=\"devicefile\">/dev/sg1</filename>, If it "
#| "still doesn't work, try typing <userinput>audiocd:/?device=/dev/sg0</"
#| "userinput> (or similar) to tell kio_audiocd which device your &CD-ROM; is."
msgid ""
"Try running <userinput><command>cdparanoia</command> <option>-vsQ</option></"
"userinput> as yourself (not <systemitem class=\"username\">root</"
"systemitem>). Do you see a track list? If not, make sure you have permission "
"to access the <acronym>CD</acronym> device. If you're using <acronym>SCSI</"
"acronym> emulation (possible if you have an <acronym>IDE</acronym> "
"<acronym>CD</acronym> writer) then make sure you check that you have read "
"and write permissions on the generic <acronym>SCSI</acronym> device, which "
"is probably <filename class=\"devicefile\">/dev/sg0</filename>, <filename "
"class=\"devicefile\">/dev/sg1</filename>, &etc; If it still doesn't work, "
"try typing <userinput>audiocd:/?device=/dev/sg0</userinput> (or similar) to "
"tell kio_audiocd which device your &CD-ROM; is."
msgstr ""
"Pokušaj uključiti <userinput><command>cdparanoja</command> <option>-vsQ</"
"option></userinput> sam (ne <systemitem class=\"username\">root</"
"systemitem>). Vidite li listu traka? Ako ne, budite sigurni da imate dozvolu "
"za pristupanje <acronym>CD</acronym> uređaju. Ako koristite  <acronym>SCSI</"
"acronym> imitaciju ( vjerovatno ako imate <acronym>IDE</acronym> "
"<acronym>CD</acronym> čitač) onda provjerite da li ste pročitali i napisali "
"dozvole za generički  <acronym>SCSI</acronym> uređaj, koji vjerovatno  "
"<filename class=\"devicefile\">/dev/sg0</filename>, <filename class="
"\"devicefile\">/dev/sg1</filename>, ako i dalje ne radi, pokušajte upisati "
"<userinput>audiocd:/?device=/dev/sg0</userinput> (ili slično) da kažete "
"kio_audiocd koji je vaš &CD-ROM; uređaj."
